		Here, we list all repositories that are usually used by NightLabs. It is urgently recommended,
		that you declare a mirror in your local settings.xml and do not directly download from these
		repositories. The reason is that 1st not all repositories are available at all times and 2nd
		many repositories are pretty slow.

		Example mirrors declaration in ~/.m2/settings.xml:

			<mirrors>
				<mirror>
					<mirrorOf>*</mirrorOf>
					<id>host.domain.tld-repo</id>
					<url>http://host.domain.tld/maven-repository/repo</url>
				</mirror>
			</mirrors>

		However, even without such a mirror, this pom.xml should build everywhere, if all used
		repositories are online & available.
		-->
